    <abstract>
      <p>RBscore&amp;NBench combines a web server, RBscore and a database, NBench. RBscore predicts RNA-/DNA-binding residues in proteins and visualizes the prediction scores and features on protein structures. The scoring scheme of RBscore directly links feature values to nucleic acid binding probabilities and illustrates the nucleic acid binding energy funnel on the protein surface. To avoid dataset, binding site definition and assessment metric biases, we compared RBscore with 18 web servers and 3 stand-alone programs on 41 datasets, which demonstrated the high and stable accuracy of RBscore. A comprehensive comparison led us to develop a benchmark database named NBench. The web server is available on: <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://ahsoka.u-strasbg.fr/rbscorenbench/">http://ahsoka.u-strasbg.fr/rbscorenbench/</ext-link>.</p>
    </abstract>
